programmes.show_description: First up, Brenton is challenged with restoring a vintage vest pocket Kodak camera. Plus, ceramics expert Kirsty pieces together a decorative marble platter.
Around the world, there are extraordinary building mistakes. Design teams and experts analyse what went wrong and how engineers are fixing them.
Host Ron Pitts brings clip after clip of the most shocking destructions caught on tape and explores the cause behind the effect of those catastrophes.
Host Ron Pitts brings clip after clip of the most shocking destructions caught on tape and explores the cause behind the effect of those catastrophes.
Ron Pitts goes behind the scenes of more moments of destruction, including, storm chasers who become storm victims, a paint factory that explodes and a plane crash at sea.
Ron Pitts delivers more incredible images of destruction caught on camera, including two Porsches colliding at triple digit speed and a massive explosion at a refinery.
More everyday items go under the microscope. How are objects including traditional Basque ham and chisteras made?
More everyday items go under the microscope. How are objects including asphalt pavers, and Basque espadrilles made?
Teleshopping.
Teleshopping.
The team restores a 1950s hot towel machine for a family of Cypriot barbers, a ceramic poppy created for the WW1 centenary and a precious portrait.
A Mouse In The Table. Drew accepts a private invitation to one of the grandest stately homes in the country, Palace House. He is stunned by a large collection of electric light fittings.
Knock From The Past. On a trip to Sheffield, Drew tries to agree a deal on some incredible industrial pieces. Later, he checks out a collection of unusual hunting artefacts in Ludlow.
Three Men And Gold. Deep in Western Australia's Goldfields, three teams of hardcore gold prospectors risk their dreams and futures, in pursuit of the ultimate reward.
A High-Stakes Gamble. Mechanical disasters and a high-stakes gamble threaten to derail the gold season for Dirt Dogs, Vern and Leon and Gold Gypsies, Chris and Greg.
The Bushmen clash with opal thieves raiding one of their mines. The Cookes hack an old digging machine, while the Fire Crew hunt for a deposit of rare black opal.
Bushmen Rod and Les risk their lives reopening a long-abandoned mine. New team the Young Guns go deep underground for the first time, hunting pineapple opal.
The team restores a 1950s hot towel machine for a family of Cypriot barbers, a ceramic poppy created for the WW1 centenary and a precious portrait.
Ford Transit. Henry and Fuzz visit Warwickshire to revive a battered Ford Transit. Once a workhorse of Britain, now a rusted relic longing for a second life.
Andy And Tim / Petrol Pump. Henry and Fuzz head for Suffolk to rummage through Andy and Tim's collection of vintage vehicles, eccentric oddities and exquisite automobilia.
Mandy / Ariel Motorbike. Henry and Sam go to Hull to meet Mandy, whose late husband was an avid collector of classic motorbikes. There are several rare Vincents and Ariels on offer.
Dad's Valuable Hoard. Angus clears a collection of ancient artefacts from the home of a legendary musician. He then helps sisters part with their aunt's treasures.
Copper Kettle Cupid. Angus visits a house packed to the rafters with vintage copper. Then he helps a couple clear their home before they relocate to Thailand.
A Hair-Raising Road Trip. Experts Raj Bisram and Irita Marriott hit the road again, winding each other up, cracking bad jokes and looking for exquisite antiques in Wales.
Small And Dainty. Raj and Irita look for antique goodies in Wales, but finding beautiful things that don't need two strong assistants to carry them isn't easy.
Will Ralph. Henry and Fuzz visit a farm near Colchester with vintage tractors galore. The boys come away with a classic Fordson and some old traffic lights.
Robin Burford. The boys visit Rob, who has an impressive collection of vintage British bikes. They find a BSA Bantam and a classic 1930's Austin Ten automobile.
Drop It Low, Drop It Slow. Guz fits air ride suspension to his Honda S2000, explores slammed car culture, and takes a £750k Porsche for a spin - very carefully.
Dara Ó Briain hosts hilarious chat and games with guests Rhys James, Angela Barnes, Alasdair Beckett-King, Ria Lina, Sean McLoughlin and Mark Simmons.
How do pilots perform jaw-dropping aerobatic stunts at supersonic speeds without crashing? How can a ski slope in the desert be kept cool? And how is sushi made?
How do they turn the trash from the world's biggest St Patrick's Day parade into power, transform a luxury limo into a racing car and craft the ultimate supersteel sword?
How do they make the world's most famous hat, and does it really hold ten gallons? Plus, how do they repair cables on the sea floor and feed 100,000 aeroplane passengers a day?
How do they stop planes from icing up; how is clay used to keep glossy magazines looking sharp; and how do they build an electric car that can reach 200kmph?
Land Rover Discovery. Mike is seduced by a Land Rover Discovery Mk1 with low mileage. But with no MOT, a leaking sunroof and rust problems, Elvis faces a big challenge.
Audi RS 6. Mike and Elvis have one of their toughest challenges yet: can they make an Audi RS6 estate car faster than a sportscar? Elvis has doubts after a hazardous test drive.
Ford Transit. Henry and Fuzz visit Warwickshire to revive a battered Ford Transit. Once a workhorse of Britain, now a rusted relic longing for a second life.
More everyday items go under the microscope. What are the production processes behind common objects including wood panel canvases and shoelaces?
More everyday items go under the microscope. What are the production processes behind common objects including Asian bowl meals and walking canes?
Teleshopping.
Teleshopping.
Dominic and Tim are challenged to restore a vintage slot machine. David rescues a worn-out bass guitar, while Suzie works on a hand-carved belt.
A Rare Breed. In Newcastle, Drew goes on a spending spree to replenish his stock of Victorian furniture. Then, he tours a grand but neglected estate to uncover any hidden gems.
The Sculpture Garden. Drew finds an impressive collection of antiques at an 18th century manor. Plus, he checks out a garden filled with more than 200 life-sized sculptures.
Pull Up The Roots. The Dirt Dogs are forced to uproot their entire operation. The Gold Gypsies face a major decision. Henri and Kelli strike salt-lake gold.
Once In A Lifetime. Torrential rain threatens to drown the Dirt Dog's season. Henri and Kellie hit a hot streak. The Gold Gypsies strike a once-in-a-lifetime find.
Rookie team the Young Guns have a life-threatening moment hunting legendary pineapple opal. The Cooke Bros scramble to hunt on another miner's claim for a share of the find.
The Tunnel Rats blast their way to a fortune and solo prospector Col Duff is stranded deep in the Queensland outback. Rookie Sam runs out of air underground.
Dominic and Tim are challenged to restore a vintage slot machine. David rescues a worn-out bass guitar, while Suzie works on a hand-carved belt.
Henry Cole and the team take on a classic 1950s Massey Ferguson combine harvester in one of their biggest restorations yet.
Dino / Morgan Sports Car. Henry and Fuzz are in West Sussex at Dino's mega-shed. He's got buses, vintage sports cars, rare motorbikes and oodles of motoring ephemera.
Chopper Roy / Triton And Bantam. Henry and Fuzz head to 'Chopper Roy's' place. His vintage British motorbikes and a classic seventies sports coupé catch their eye.
A Gold Medal & A Hand Grenade. A surprise find in a client's garden has Angus's team stunned, but will a big silver key unlock a generous donation to a worthy charity?
Yorkshire's Greatest Showman. Angus receives a call from two sisters desperate to find new homes for their late father's incredible collection of circus memorabilia.
A Precious Metal Extravaganza. It's all gold and silver on Raj's and Irita's third leg. They find their groove in Birmingham's reggae heartland before a surprise auction result.
Secret Doors And Time Travel. Raj and Irita embark on a five-county tour of The Fens. On the way, they'll discover secret doors, prehistoric artefacts and time travel.
Standard Teignmouth. Henry and Fuzz find a rare 1929 Standard Teignmouth pick-up. Intrigued by this unusual beast, can they figure out what they're going to do with it?
Mum Knows Best. Things appear to be on the up when they land a prestigious Morgan job, but a disastrous E-Type re-build prompts an emergency audit by Richard's mum.
Drop It Low, Drop It Slow. Guz fits air ride suspension to his Honda S2000, explores slammed car culture, and takes a £750k Porsche for a spin - very carefully.
How do they provide services in one of the world's largest casino hotels, cut through metal with a beam of light, and build a golf course in the desert?
How do they drill through a kilometre of solid rock, pick 20,000 oranges a minute for juice, and get glass to curve without cracking?
